    "summary": "Gladney Center for Adoption, HQ: Ft Worth, TX, NAICS 624110 (nonresidential social assistance services for children and youth, including adoption, foster care, and drug prevention), EMP: 115. On June 25, 2025, cybersecurity researcher Jeremiah Fowler discovered a massive set of unprotected records linked to the Gladney Center for Adoption, left online without a password, without encryption, and accessible to anyone. The database contained2.49 gigabytes and holding more than 1,115,061 records included deeply sensitive information about children, adoptive parents, birth families, internal staff, names and contact details to case notes and private assessments, folders labeled “contacts”, “applications”, and “birth fathers”, reason for adoption denials, personal histories, family backgrounds, substance use, emails, and legal matters.",
